## Task 4: Update Blog Card Image Logic

### Current Problem
Blog cards use hero image from frontmatter. Need to use random image from blog post instead.

### Requirements

#### 4.1 Current Behavior
**File**: `src/components/Blog/BlogCard.tsx` (and similar)

Currently shows:
```typescript
<Image src={post.image} alt={post.imageAlt} />
```

#### 4.2 New Behavior
Show random image from blog post images instead of hero.

**Logic**:
```typescript
// Get all images from post
const postImages = post.carouselImages || [];

// If carouselImages exist, pick random one
// Otherwise fall back to hero image
const displayImage = postImages.length > 0 
  ? postImages[Math.floor(Math.random() * postImages.length)]
  : { url: post.image, alt: post.imageAlt };
```

#### 4.3 Implementation Strategy

**Option A: Client-side Random (changes on refresh)**
```typescript
'use client';
import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';

export default function BlogCard({ post }) {
  const [displayImage, setDisplayImage] = useState(post.image);
  
  useEffect(() => {
    if (post.carouselImages?.length > 0) {
      const random = post.carouselImages[
        Math.floor(Math.random() * post.carouselImages.length)
      ];
      setDisplayImage(random.url);
    }
  }, [post]);
  
  return <Image src={displayImage} ... />;
}
```

**Option B: Server-side Random (consistent per build)**
```typescript
// In parent component or lib function
function getRandomPostImage(post: BlogMetadata) {
  if (!post.carouselImages || post.carouselImages.length === 0) {
    return { url: post.image, alt: post.imageAlt };
  }
  
  // Use post slug as seed for consistent randomness
  const seed = post.slug.split('').reduce((a, b) => a + b.charCodeAt(0), 0);
  const index = seed % post.carouselImages.length;
  
  return post.carouselImages[index];
}
```

**Recommendation**: Use Option B (server-side) for:
- Consistent images across page loads
- Better SEO (stable image URLs)
- No client-side hydration flash

#### 4.4 Components to Update
**Update all blog card components**:
